  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "\n<p><b>Type:</b> Taijutsu (Strike)</p>\n<p><b>Rank:</b> 1</p>\n<p><b>Chakra Cost:</b> 10</p>\n\n<p><b>Learn DC:</b>  | <b>Successes:</b> </p>\n<p><b>Perform:</b> 9 | <b>Perform DC:</b> 21</p>\n\n<p><b>Components:</b> M, F, Mas</p>\n\n<hr>\n\n<p>A technique similar to Shuugeki Tou Sei, Shouha Tou Sei gets power from a push of the user's other hand increasing the strength of this overhead slash. This technique acts like Shuugeki Tou Sei but the additional damage is 1d6 damage per 3 levels of the user (max 5d6, not multiplied on critical hit). Additionally, the attack has its critical multiplier increased by 1 (from x 2 to x3).</p>\n\n<hr><p><b>Requires:</b> : Watou Jutsu - Shuugeki Tou Sei (2)</p>\n<p><b>Mastery:</b> First, third and fifth step of mastery in this technique increase the cap of additional damage by 1d6 (up to a total of 8d6 at fifth step).<br><br>With the fourth step of mastery in this technique the user can use it as a part of a charge, but doing so increases Perform DC by 7, and Chakra Cost by 2. If the technique is used this way, the user cannot convert the cost to hit points.<br><br>Material Focus -The user's Wato, katana, double katana or hansori.</p>\n",
      "summary": "",
      "instructions": ""
    },
